   "source": [
    "# Raw data\n",
    "_Raw data_ are collected data that have not been organized numerically. An example is the set of heights of $100$ maile students obtained from an alphabetical listing of university records.\n",
    "\n",
    "In R, raw data can be assembled into `vectors`, `data-frames`, or `matrices`."
   ]
